<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Read More Effect</title>
    <style>
        .content {
            height: 100px; /* Limit height initially */
            overflow: hidden;
            transition: height 0.3s ease-in-out;
        }

        .read-more-btn {
            display: block;
            cursor: pointer;
            color: blue;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 10px;
            border: none;
            background: none;
        }
		#extraContent
		{
		 height: 200px;
		}
		
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="content" id="textContent">
        <p>
            Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed euismod, nisl eget facilisis ultricies, 
            nibh lorem aliquet nisl, eu sodales elit diam vel dolor. Curabitur non libero ut ipsum sagittis tincidunt.
            Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. 
            Integer euismod elit in tellus suscipit, ac facilisis orci consectetur.
            <span id="extraContent" style="display: none;height:200px;">
                <br><br>
                More hidden text here! This part was hidden but now it's visible.
                Vestibulum ante ipsum primis in faucibus orci luctus et ultrices posuere cubilia curae; 
                Donec vitae neque nec nunc ullamcorper tincidunt. 
                Proin elementum, turpis sed efficitur luctus, erat justo pulvinar sapien, sit amet dapibus odio metus ut libero.
            </span>
        </p>
    </div>
    <button class="read-more-btn" onclick="toggleReadMore()">Read More</button>

    <script>
        function toggleReadMore() {
            var extraContent = document.getElementById("extraContent");
            var button = document.querySelector(".read-more-btn");

            if (extraContent.style.display === "none") {
                extraContent.style.display = "inline"; // Show hidden text
                button.textContent = "Read Less"; 
            } else {
                extraContent.style.display = "none"; // Hide text again
                button.textContent = "Read More"; 
            }
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
